{
  "texts": [
    "DTAM-SLAM, which stands for dense tracking and mapping, is a V-SLAM algorithm specified for real-time camera tracking.",
    "It provides robust six degrees of freedom (6 DoF) tracking and facilitates efficient environmental modeling for robotic systems (Ne. et al., 2011; Macario Barros et al., 2022).",
    "This approach plays a fundamental role in advancing applications such as robotics, augmented reality, and autonomous navigation, delivering precise tracking and high-quality map reconstruction.",
    "Furthermore, it is slightly dynamic with light; thus, it is accurate to operate in high and strong illumination fields (Zhu et al., 2022; Yang et al., 2022); see Table 2.",
    "The DTAM-SLAM workflow is divided into a series of steps, each with its own purpose (Ne et al., 2011; Macario Barros et al., 2022)."
  ]
}